==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Responsory
<hw>Re*spon"so*ry</hw> <pr>(r?*sp?n"s?*r?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Containing or making answer; answering.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Responsory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Responsory
<hw>Re*spon"so*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>-ries</plw> <pr>(-r<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL.
<ets>responsorium</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The answer of the people to the priest in alternate
speaking, in church service.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A versicle sung in
answer to the priest, or as a refrain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which, if should repeat again, would turn my answers into
<qex>responsories</qex>, and beget another liturgy.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>An antiphonary; a response
book.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ressaldar</ent>⟦br⟧
